---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | SciCalcX Online Computational Suite" description="Review the SciCalcX Privacy Policy. Learn about local storage usage, cookies, and Google AdSense third-party advertising disclosures.">
  <div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 sm:space-y-8 font-sans">
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="text-center md:text-left space-y-1.5 border-b border-brand-border/60 pb-4">
      <div class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-blue-neon">
        Legal & Compliance
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-text">
        Privacy Policy<span class="text-brand-blue">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-brand-text-muted">
        Last Updated: July 22, 2026. Learn how we respect your computational privacy and handle data.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Privacy details -->
    <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-gray-dark/40 rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 space-y-6 shadow-xl backdrop-blur-sm leading-relaxed text-sm text-brand-text-muted">
      
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          1. Introduction
        </h2>
        <p>
          Welcome to SciCalcX (the "Platform", accessible via <a href="https://scicalcx.com" class="text-brand-blue-neon hover:underline">scicalcx.com</a>). We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting any personal information you may share with us. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, protect, and disclose information when you interact with our suite of scientific calculators, programmers tools, calculus widgets, and interactive code tutor environments.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          2. Computational Privacy & Client-Side Logic
        </h2>
        <p>
          At SciCalcX, we strongly believe that your calculations, formulas, systems code, and matrices are strictly your own property. 
        </p>
        <p>
          To ensure maximum speed, security, and privacy, all computations, token parsing, and code compilations are executed <strong>directly within your local web browser engine</strong>. We do not transmit, analyze, collect, or store any of the formula inputs, mathematical values, compiler entries, or data structures on our servers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          3. Local Storage Usage
        </h2>
        <p>
          We utilize browser `localStorage` features solely to enhance your user experience. This allows the Platform to persist your settings between sessions without requiring you to create an account. This features includes:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1.5 text-xs">
          <li><strong>Theme Preferences:</strong> Dark mode and light mode configuration attributes.</li>
          <li><strong>Calculation History:</strong> A rolling log of your previous inputs and outputs (capped at 50 records) so you can easily review and reload prior calculations.</li>
          <li><strong>Memory Values:</strong> Standard memory values saved via algebraic memory operations (M+, M-, MR).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data remains localized within your web browser environment. You can clear your localStorage data at any time by clicking the [Clear All] button in the history sidebar, or by clearing your browser's site data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          4. Google AdSense & Third-Party Advertising Disclosures
        </h2>
        <p>
          To support the development and maintenance of SciCalcX, we display advertisements provided by third-party ad networks, including Google AdSense. In compliance with Google's publisher policies, please read the following disclosures:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1.5 text-xs">
          <li>
            <strong>Third-Party Cookies:</strong> Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to SciCalcX or other websites on the Internet.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Personalized Advertising:</strong> Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve personalized ads to you based on your visits to our Platform and/or other sites on the Internet.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Opt-Out Procedures:</strong> You may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting Google's <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand-blue-neon hover:underline">Ads Settings</a>. Alternatively, you can opt out of a third-party vendor's use of cookies for personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand-blue-neon hover:underline">About Ads Choices</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          5. Web Analytics & Log Data
        </h2>
        <p>
          We may deploy privacy-first web analytics services (such as Google Analytics) to help us measure traffic patterns, site speed, and general usage trends. These services use anonymous cookies to gather basic information, such as browser types, referring pages, search queries, and operating systems. We use this information solely to monitor performance, squash bugs, and optimize SciCalcX.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          6. External Links
        </h2>
        <p>
          Our Platform may contain links to external web resources (such as GitHub or educational articles). Please note that we have no control over, and assume no responsibility for, the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party websites or services. We encourage you to read the privacy policies of any site you visit.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          7. Children's Privacy
        </h2>
        <p>
          SciCalcX does not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from children under the age of 13. If you are under 13, please do not attempt to send any personal information about yourself to us. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will delete that information as quickly as possible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          8. Changes to this Privacy Policy
        </h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time to reflect changes in our operational guidelines, legal requirements, or integration partners. We will notify you of any revisions by updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
          9. Contact Information
        </h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions or feedback regarding this Privacy Policy or our computational practices, please feel free to reach out to us:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-2 font-mono text-xs border border-brand-border bg-brand-black/40 p-3 rounded">
          <span class="block"><strong class="text-white">Email Support:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@scicalcx.com" class="text-brand-blue-neon hover:underline">support@scicalcx.com</a></span>
          <span class="block mt-1"><strong class="text-white">Open Source:</strong> <a href="#" class="text-brand-blue-neon hover:underline">GitHub Repository</a></span>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
